ed through the interplay of meaningful voices and meaningful silences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCollective memoryzNetherlands. 0aPostcolonialismzNetherlands. 4a20th century, c 1900 to c 1999. 4a21st century, c 2000 to c 2100. 4aAsian history. 4aContemporary Society. 4aDutch and The Netherlands. 4aHeritage Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aNational liberation and independence. 4aNetherlands. 4aSociety and culture: general. 4aSouth East Asia. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Western.2bisacsh  aCultural heritage, Colonial memory, Moluccan community in the Netherlands, Postcolonial identity, Diaspora.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076709408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048555796zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048555796zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048555796/original  a978-3-11-076700-1 DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076709-4 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA